(802, 1, '2015-03-11 16:32:08', '2015-03-11 16:32:08', 'Global Exteriors has been serving Saskatoon since 1994. Over the years, owners and brothers Brian and Andy Fehr have grown the business from a few small teams to managing more than a dozen crews. With more than 20 years spent working in Saskatoon, we have long relationships with some of the top home builders in the city.\r\n\r\nOur specialty is residential exteriors: new and renovated, multi-family and single home. We are experts in siding and soffit, windows and doors, and eavestroughs and insulation. But if you need exterior work done outside our expertise -- like stonework, roofing, or building an addition -- we have access to companies we trust who can finish the job.\r\n\r\nAndy and Brian started in the housing industry working with their dad, and they stayed in the family line of work. Brian worked in siding installation for 15 years before starting Global Exteriors with Andy. Their time on the ground has given them a product knowledge that''s hard to beat. Global Exteriors only provides the best products on the market.\r\n\r\nWe ensure quality workmanship through careful oversight. A foreman visits our sites daily, and every site is inspected by either Andy or Brian upon completion. We also have a full time service person available to answer any questions once the work is done.\r\n\r\n[HEADER] COMMUNITY OUTREACH\r\nGlobal Exteriors is a community-minded company; we want to improve the quality of both the homes we work on, and the neighbourhoods where our clients live. To that end, we support Youth for Christ Saskatoon [LINK: http://yfcsask.com/], the local chapter of a worldwide Christian movement. Andy has sat on the YFC Sask board of directors for more than a decade, helping to organize tons of fun experiences and activities for kids, including our newest initiative, the Mobile Youth Centre. [LINK: http://yfcsask.com/mobile-youth-centre] \r\n\r\n[SUGGESTION: Put blurb about job opportunities under staff photo?]\r\n\r\n[HEADER] WANT TO JOIN THE TEAM?\r\nWe are looking for both employees and subcontractors with appropriate experience who want to work in a fast-paced, well-organized work environment. If you’re interested in joining our team, please drop off a resume at our office at 833 Cynthia Street, or send a resume to Brian at brian@globalexteriors.com. \r\n', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-11 16:32:08', '2015-03-11 16:32:08', '', 13, 'http://localhost/global-exteriors/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(803, 1, '2015-03-11 16:33:15', '2015-03-11 16:33:15', 'SERVICES AND PRODUCTS\r\n\r\nWhether we’re doing the installation ourselves or helping you DIY, Global Exteriors only offers the best products. We have access to a wide variety of suppliers, tapping Canada’s top brands to outfit your home’s exterior. \r\n\r\n[HEADER] SERVICES\r\n\r\nVINYL SIDING\r\nThe popular choice among today’s consumers, vinyl siding requires little maintenance and is ideal for Saskatchewan’s tough climate.\r\n\r\nSOFFIT, FASCIA, AND TRIM\r\nA vital element to any home’s appearance, our top-quality soffit, fascia, and trim products add that perfect finishing touch.\r\n\r\nWINDOWS AND DOORS\r\nEnhance the look of your home while improving energy efficiency. We can provide any style you want for your home. \r\n\r\nEAVESTROUGHS\r\nAll of our eavestroughs are expertly crafted in-house in a wide range of colours and sizes to suit all of your needs. \r\n\r\n[HEADER] PRODUCTS\r\n\r\n[SUB-HEAD] KAYCAN\r\nTimberlake siding\r\nDaVinci siding\r\nHardwood Valley\r\nRichmond Ultra\r\nKWP engineered wood siding\r\nKWP wood trims\r\nPerfection shingle shakes\r\nVertical and board and batten siding\r\nEco siding engineered wood siding\r\n\r\n[SUB-HEAD] GENTEK\r\nDriftwood siding\r\nSequoia siding\r\nNorthern Forest Elite siding\r\nProdigy siding\r\nBoard and batten siding\r\nAllura siding\r\nHardie board siding\r\nFoundry shakes\r\nLongboard aluminum siding and soffit\r\nGentek windows & doors\r\nVersetta stone faux cement stone panels\r\nRockford stone faux stone panels\r\n\r\n[SUB-HEAD] MITTEN \r\nSentry siding\r\nHighland siding\r\nCambridge siding\r\nOregon pride siding\r\nSouthern beaded siding\r\nVertical and board and batten siding\r\nInsuplank\r\nGenstone faux stone panels\r\n', 'Services & Products', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '15-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-11 16:33:15', '2015-03-11 16:33:15', '', 15, 'http://localhost/global-exteriors/15-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(804, 1, '2015-03-11 16:34:24', '2015-03-11 16:34:24', 'Are you ready to DIY? Installing siding yourself can save you money, but before you embark on a project check your skill level: Do you feel confident? Have you done projects like this before? Are you a naturally handy or crafty person?\r\n\r\nIf so, great! The next step is preparation. Vinyl siding is the best choice for do-it-yourself projects because it''s easier to remove, alter, and reinstall than any other type of siding, and the only special tool you''ll need for the job is an unlocking tool, or zip tool.\r\n\r\nWe have some great sources to help guide you through the process:\r\nGentek Vinyl Products Installation Guide [LINK TO PDF]\r\nKaycan Vinyl Siding Estimating and Installation Guide [LINK TO PDF]\r\nMitten How to Install Guide: Prepare, Install & Care for your New Vinyl Siding [LINK TO PDF]\r\n\r\nOnce you have a plan in place, you''ll need to choose the right materials. That''s where the experts at Global Exteriors come in. We have a full range of DIY-friendly products, which you can see in our showroom, and we''re happy to give advice and answer any questions you have.\r\n\r\n[USE SHOWROOM PICTURE AROUND HERE? Because the paragraph above mentions the show room.]\r\n\r\nSiding is like putting together a big puzzle, and it''s even easier with the right guidance from experts who have tackled the challenge before.\r\n\r\nSo what are you waiting for? Get a siding estimate [LINK TO ESTIMATE PAGE], or give us a ring [LINK TO CONTACT PAGE] if you have any questions.\r\n', 'DIY Tips', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-11 16:34:24', '2015-03-11 16:34:24', '', 60, 'http://localhost/global-exteriors/60-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
