(833, 1, '2015-03-11 22:19:26', '2015-03-11 22:19:26', 'Are you ready to DIY? Installing siding yourself can save you money, but before you embark on a project check your skill level: Do you feel confident? Have you done projects like this before? Are you a naturally handy or crafty person?\r\n\r\nIf so, great! The next step is preparation. Vinyl siding is the best choice for do-it-yourself projects because it''s easier to remove, alter, and reinstall than any other type of siding, and the only special tool you''ll need for the job is an unlocking tool, or zip tool.\r\n\r\nWe have some great sources to help guide you through the process:\r\nGentek Vinyl Products Installation Guide [LINK TO PDF]\r\nKaycan Vinyl Siding Estimating and Installation Guide [LINK TO PDF]\r\nMitten How to Install Guide: Prepare, Install &amp; Care for your New Vinyl Siding [LINK TO PDF]\r\n\r\nOnce you have a plan in place, you''ll need to choose the right materials. That''s where the experts at Global Exteriors come in. We have a full range of DIY-friendly products, which you can see in our showroom, and we''re happy to give advice and answer any questions you have.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost/global-exteriors/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/showroom-pics.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-187" src="http://localhost/global-exteriors/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/showroom-pics-1024x683.jpg" alt="showroom pics" width="1024" height="683" /></a>\r\n\r\nSiding is like putting together a big puzzle, and it''s even easier with the right guidance from experts who have tackled the challenge before.\r\n\r\nSo what are you waiting for? Get a siding estimate [LINK TO ESTIMATE PAGE], or give us a ring [LINK TO CONTACT PAGE] if you have any questions.', 'DIY Tips', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-11 22:19:26', '2015-03-11 22:19:26', '', 60, 'http://localhost/global-exteriors/60-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
